# TP1: HDFS File System Manipulation

This project contains the commands and scripts needed to perform a set of operations on the Hadoop Distributed File System (HDFS).

## Description

This practical work covers basic HDFS operations:
- Creating a directory structure
- Creating and manipulating files
- Copying files from the local system to HDFS
- Deleting and renaming files
- Recursively exploring content

## Prerequisites

- Docker and Docker Compose
- Apache Hadoop Docker image: `apache/hadoop:3.3.6`

## Cluster Configuration

The project uses Docker Compose to deploy a complete Hadoop cluster including:
- 1 namenode
- 5 datanodes
- 1 resourcemanager
- 1 nodemanager

## Quick Start

1. Clone this repository
```bash
git clone <repository_URL>
cd hadoop-hdfs-tp1
```

2. Launch the cluster
```bash
docker-compose up -d
```

3. Execute HDFS commands
```bash
docker exec -it namenode bash /opt/script/hdfs_tp.sh
```

4. Access the HDFS web interface
```
http://localhost:9870
```

## Practical Work Content

The practical work includes the following operations:
1. Creating a directory structure
2. Creating and manipulating files
3. Displaying file contents
4. Copying files between HDFS directories
5. Renaming and deleting files
6. Transferring files from the local system to HDFS
7. Recursively exploring the directory structure
8. Deleting directories

## Project Structure

```
hadoop-hdfs/
├── docker-compose.yml
├── configuration/
│   └── config
├── images/
│   └── image.pmg
├── scripts/
│   └── hdfs_tp.sh
└── README.md
```

